title: Part of Old Fortress, Honfleur
medium: Graphite on thick cream wove paper tipped into binding with fabric
description: Vertical sheet depicting a large, medieval masonry structure with many later Renaissance and Baroque additions.  The mass of the building on the right is only sketched so as to understand its volume, while the section of the building at left has been fully rendered to capture the details of the rusticated stonework, the arched entrance and wood doors, a canon, and the irregularities of the roofline with its chimneys and turrets.
name: Album page
